[[!meta title="Numerous security holes in previous amnesia versions"]]
[[!pagetemplate template="news.tmpl"]]

[[!tag security/fixed]]

The following security holes affect *amnesia* systems older than 0.5.

We **strongly** urge you to [[upgrade to T(A)ILS 0.5|news/version_0.5]] in
case you are still using an older version.

- ffmpeg: [DSA-2000](http://www.debian.org/security/2010/dsa-2000)
- polipo: [DSA-2002](http://www.debian.org/security/2010/dsa-2002)
- Linux kernel:
  [DSA-2003](http://www.debian.org/security/2010/dsa-2003),
  [DSA-2012](http://www.debian.org/security/2010/dsa-2012),
  [DSA-1996](http://www.debian.org/security/2010/dsa-1996)
- cups: [DSA-2007](http://www.debian.org/security/2010/dsa-2007)
- dpkg: [DSA-2011](http://www.debian.org/security/2010/dsa-2011)
- curl: [DSA-2023](http://www.debian.org/security/2010/dsa-2023)
- iceweasel: [DSA-2027](http://www.debian.org/security/2010/dsa-2027),
  [DSA-1999](http://www.debian.org/security/2010/dsa-1999)
- libpng: [DSA-2032](http://www.debian.org/security/2010/dsa-2032)
- pidgin: [DSA-2038](http://www.debian.org/security/2010/dsa-2038)
- openoffice.org: [DSA-1995](http://www.debian.org/security/2010/dsa-1995)
